rComments: Incredibly boring... lectures were simple slides, she seemed under prepared with not enough material to talk about. She cut any discussion short and really limited critical thinking in the class. I'm not sure anyone in the class could say they enjoyed it. I was really interested in the topic, but she kinda killed any excitement I had.
She had less insight than my 10 year old brother. She was also disorganized, had little to say in lectures, and took forever to reply to emails. Not a UofT level professor at all.

the most insensitive professor I've ever had, she taught African American history without ever self-identifying herself and consistently referred to Blues music as 'silly'- can't believe she works at a university
